multiLocaleSummary.en_US: I'm an IT and Network professional with hands-on experience in managing enterprise IT infrastructure, implementing security tools like Fortinet firewalls, and supporting cloud migration projects. Currently working with CARE International, I’ve independently handled full office setups, user support, and procurement for international donor-funded projects. My strengths lie in network troubleshooting, Microsoft EMS user management, and providing remote and on-site support to field teams. With a degree in Computer System Engineering and a background that includes technical writing and web development, I focus on practical, reliable, and secure IT solutions that keep operations running smoothly. Always open to learning and applying new technologies in real-world environments.
